- "neglected, like forgotten flowers" refers to devices that have not been checked in the last 30 days;
- "sounded the alarm" refers to the number of alerts generated by the device;
- "from the most troublesome to the least" means the results are ordered by the alert count in descending order.

- "guardians of the air" refers to devices that measure air quality;
- "highest breath of carbon monoxide" refers to the highest CO level;
- "whisper of pollution exceeds 10 ppm" refers to CO levels greater than 10 ppm.

- "Active devices" are those with a status of 'active';
- "Alerts" are triggered when the carbon monoxide, temperature, or smoke levels exceed predefined thresholds;
- "Most recent measurements" are determined by the latest timestamp for each device.

- 'active devices' refers to devices whose status is 'active';
- 'average temperature' is calculated from the temperature measurements;
- 'alerts' are triggered based on certain conditions, such as high temperature or carbon monoxide levels;
- '2022' is the year between January 1, 2022, and December 31, 2022.

- Active devices are those whose status is 'active';
- Indoor devices are those whose location is 'indoor';
- Resolved alerts are those whose status is 'resolved'.

- "sentinels of the air" refers to the devices that measure carbon monoxide levels;
- "breathing the most toxic fumes" refers to having the highest average CO levels;
- "breaths of poison" refers to the average carbon monoxide levels measured;
- "over the past month" refers to the last 30 days.

- "steady heartbeat" refers to the average battery level of the device;
- "traveled the lowest ground" refers to the minimum altitude of the device;
- "collected a significant number of data points" refers to the total count of measurements;
- "more than 10 stories to tell" refers to the condition that the device must have more than 10 measurements;
- "strength of their heartbeat" refers to the average battery level, which is used for sorting in descending order.
